13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Coverage of certain treatments and medications relating to diabetes
14 and obesity and polycystic ovary syndrome -- state group insurance. (1) (a) Each individual disability
15 policy, certificate of insurance, and membership contract that is delivered, issued for delivery, renewed,
16 extended, or modified in this state An insurance contract or plan issued under this part must provide coverage
17 for:
18 (i) glucagon-like peptide-1 receptor agonists if it is determined to be medically necessary; and
19 (ii) polycystic ovary syndrome if it is determined to be medically necessary.
20 (b) For the purposes of subsection (1)(a), the term "medically necessary" includes but is not limited
21 to a diagnosis of diabetes or class 3 obesity or polycystic ovary syndrome.
22 (2) Coverage under this section may be subject to deductibles, coinsurance, and copayment
23 provisions. Special deductible, coinsurance, copayment, or other limitations that are not generally applicable to
24 other medical services covered under the plan may not be imposed on coverage of glucagon-like peptide-1
25 receptor agonists. A health insurance issuer may use cost containment measures, which may include but are
26 not limited to step therapy and prior authorization.
27 (3) This section does not apply to disability income, hospital indemnity, medicare supplement,
28 specified disease, or long-term care policies applies only to group health insurance for state employees and
